        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 7:54PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 754 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Audubon, or 10 miles
south of Chatsworth, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ellijay, Carters, Talona, Tails Creek, Ramhurst, Mountaintown,
Oakman, Fort Mountain State Park, North Georgia Speedway, Audubon,
and Roundtop.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
